on a woman printer during the handpress period. It consists of a historical essay detailing Bailey’s life and analyzing her role in the contemporary book trade, followed by a checklist of her known imprints. In addition, appendixes offer further statistical information on the activities of her shop. Together, these provide rich material for other book historians as well as for historians of the early Republic, gender, and technology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPrintingzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy19th century. 0aWomen printerszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiavBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh  aKaren Nipps Houghton.  aLibrary Fiction Pennsylvania.  aLydia Bailey: "Lydia Bailey".  aPenn State Series.  ain the History of the Book.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014z97831107452690 cprintz978027105571840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271062303?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271062303423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271062303/original  a978-3-11-074526-9  Penn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pre-2014b2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK